    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 152: <gloss
                        target="#t_SFM1">SFM</gloss> Documents 1–40</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Agenda of the Meetings of the Foreign Ministers of the United
                        States, United Kingdom, and France</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-12">September 12,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Document 1 (Revised)<note n="1" xml:id="d566fn1">The only
                        difference between Document 1 and Document 1 (Revised) is that the latter
                        bears the parenthetical phrase at the top of the agenda “(Approved at the
                        First Meeting, Tuesday, September 12, 3:00 p. m.).”</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>I—North Atlantic Treaty Questions. <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>European Defense Force.</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>Financial Questions.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <item>II—German Problems. <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>Internal Security.</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>Report of the Intergovernmental Study Group.</item>
                                <label>C.</label>
                                <item>Berlin.</item>
                                <label>D.</label>
                                <item>Miscellaneous Problems.</item>
                                <label>E.</label>
                                <item>Communiqué.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <item>III—Consideration of the security problem in the Near East with
                            particular reference to Greece and Turkey (including the Turkish request
                            for participation in the North Atlantic Treaty).</item>
                        <item>IV—Exchange of views on policy toward the Soviet Union in light of
                            recent developments.</item>
                        <item>V—Consideration of Western European Problems. <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>East–West Trade.</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>Economic assistance to Yugoslavia.</item>
                                <label>C.</label>
                                <item>Report of Tripartite Experts on European Migration.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <pb facs="1214" n="1190" xml:id="pg_1190"/>
                        <item>VI—Consideration of United Nations Problems within the context of
                            recent events. <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>The strengthening of United Nations procedures for dealing
                                    with aggression.</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>Position concerning draft resolution on Spain.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <item>VII—Consideration of Far Eastern Problems. <list>
                                <label>A.</label>
                                <item>Policy toward Southeast Asia, particularly Indochina.</item>
                                <label>B.</label>
                                <item>Korea.</item>
                                <label>C.</label>
                                <item>Formosa.</item>
                                <label>D.</label>
                                <item>Chinese representation in the United Nations.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <item>VIII—Communiqué.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
